Billabong Odyssey (2003)

: Documentary, Action, Adventure, Sport
: 2003
: Philip Boston
: Shawn Barron, Fred Basse, Layne Beachley, Ken Bradshaw
: USA
: 6.3/10
: 1h:27m

:
The most ambitious surfing video ever undertaken! Filmed over the course of two years, Billabong Odyssey explores the life-or-death adventure of a team of surfers on the quest to find and surf the biggest wave on the planet. The film tracks expeditions to a variety of exotic and contrasting locations around the world, usually at a moment's notice, led by big water superstars like Southern California's Mike Parsons and Brad Gerlach, the Santa Cruz wildmen Darryl &quot;Flea&quot; Virostko, Shawn &quot;Barney&quot; Barron, Ken &quot;Skindog&quot; Collins and Josh Loya, big-wave legend Ken Bradshaw and world champion Layne Beachley. The team challenges deadly waves throughout the world, including the mouth of the Columbia River in Washington State; Mavericks in Northern California; Todos Santos Island, Mexico; Cortes Bank in the Pacific; the outer shoals of the Hawaiian Isles of Oahu and Maui; the vicious barrels of Teahupoo, Tahiti; and newly-discovered reefs in Australia, France and Spain.

&quot;A thousand people have climbed Mount Everest, but how many people have ridden an 80-foot wave? This is something special.&quot;- Mike Parsons, professional surfer.


